definitions.definition: The part between the main part of the hindlimb and the metatarsus in terrestrial vertebrates .

subdefinitions.definition: A group of small bones in this part of the foot . The seven bones of the human tarsus form the ankle and upper part of the foot.
The shank or tarsometatarsus of the leg of a bird or reptile .
The true foot or the fifth joint of the leg of an insect or other arthropod , typically consisting of several small segments and ending in a claw .

definitions.definition: A plate of dense connective tissue found in each eyelid , attached to either the superior tarsal muscle (in the upper eyelid) or inferior tarsal muscle (lower eyelid), which aid with sympathetic control.

main_definition: ( anatomy , zootomy ) The part between the main part of the hindlimb and the metatarsus in terrestrial vertebrates .
